  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Mapping and Geospatial Analysis for First Phase Emergency Response, Preparedness and Local Capacity Building.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Key humanitarian decision makers will be able to make better decisions based on more reliable and/or relevant information, presented in appropriate visual formats, at the earliest opportunities in humanitarian emergencies, resulting in better outcomes for affected populations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MapAction has two target groups: direct service users and indirect or ultimate service users. 

Direct service users are those agencies for whom we provide direct geospatial services; 

Indirect service users are the operational agencies, both governmental and NGOs who use many of our products, and ultimately, disaster affected populations.

Ultimate services users are the affected people, but whilst they will benefit from faster and better targeted aid, they will obviously not directly require or want specialist analytical mapping and disaster IM products as much as tangible effective assistance arising from aid well directed by analytical mapping.</narrative>
  </description>
